The paper proposes an approach to detect behavioral changes in software commits, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The approach involves generating test methods through assertion amplification and search-based exploration of input spaces, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL) and software development (cs.SD). The paper also evaluates the approach on a curated set of open source Java projects, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques.
